        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2770357524" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7334594204207377081">I was really hooked on this book especially at the beginning. I sat up late the first night finding it hard to put down. After the first quarter of the story, I felt as though I was watching a Lifetime movie, but I was still interested. <br/><br/>Abbie is a doctor who is married to another doctor, Alan, a cardiologist. At the beginning of the story, she is in a terrible head-on car accident, the fault of a drunk driver. The drunk driver happens to be her husband! He does not survive the wreck and she has </span>
  <span id="freeText7334594204207377081" style="display:none">I was really hooked on this book especially at the beginning. I sat up late the first night finding it hard to put down. After the first quarter of the story, I felt as though I was watching a Lifetime movie, but I was still interested. <br /><br />Abbie is a doctor who is married to another doctor, Alan, a cardiologist. At the beginning of the story, she is in a terrible head-on car accident, the fault of a drunk driver. The drunk driver happens to be her husband! He does not survive the wreck and she has some serious injuries, but is able to be at her husband's bedside when he dies. <br /><br />There is a teenage son, Zack, who loves his father dearly, as does Abbie. When a devastating secret is revealed about her husband after his death, she is torn between loving him and hating him, and whether to reveal the secret to her son.<br /><br />It was a quick read, and did not have bad language or sex scenes. 3.5 stars rounded up to 4.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7334594204207377081" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


